it fraud</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>When you have to repay the money</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll have to pay the money back if the overpayment was your fault, eg:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the information you gave was wrong </li>\n  <li>you didn’t report a change in your circumstances</li>\n  <li>there was an administrative mistake but you should have noticed the overpayment - for example, if you receive 2 payments instead of 1</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>If your landlord gets your Housing Benefit directly</h3>\n\n<p>Your landlord may be asked to repay the money if they’re responsible for the overpayment. </p>\n\n<p>If the overpayment was your fault, you may have to repay it.</p>\n\n<h2>What happens if you’ve been overpaid</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll get a letter to let you know that you&rsquo;ve overpaid. You should contact the office dealing with your benefit within 1 month if you think this is a mistake and you want to appeal the decision.</p>\n\n<h3>Making repayments</h3>\n\n<p>If you’re still receiving the benefit, the regular amount you get will be reduced until you’ve paid back the money. </p>\n\n<p>Otherwise you’ll receive a bill. Contact the relevant office if you want to set up a payment plan.</p>\n","alternative_title":""},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:22:24+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Benefits entitlement","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits%2Fentitlement.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"When and how benefit payments are made, benefits adviser and benefit fraud","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=benefits%2Fentitlement","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/benefits/entitlement"},"parent":{"title":"Benefits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes tax credits and eligibility","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=benefits","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/benefits"},"pare